02/11/2003
DERVENTA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Presidency member Borislav Paravac expressed support Saturday (1 November) for the position of Republika Srpska President Dragan Cavic on defence reform.
Earlier in the week, Cavic urged lawmakers to pass the defence reform bill submitted by the line federal commission.
Paravac said such reforms were inevitable as they were spelled out in the guidelines for joining the Partnership for Peace approved two years ago.
(SRNA, TV1 - 01/11/03;
Onasa - 31/10/03)
